      • getConfigItems

        public final java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​com.qoretechnologies.qorus.ConfigItem> getConfigItems()
        Method to return local configuration items This is executed by oload "oload" when the object is loaded. The base class implementation returns null.
        Returns:
        a hash of local configuration items keyed by configuration item name
        Note:
        • If any configuration items have an invalid type, an error is raised
        • Child classes should override getConfigItemsImpl(); this method cannot be overridden

      • getConfigItemsImpl

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​com.qoretechnologies.qorus.ConfigItem> getConfigItemsImpl()
        Method to return local configuration items; this method should be overridden by child classes to provide item configuration This is executed by getConfigItems() by oload when the object is loaded into the system. The base class implementation is empty and returns null.
        Returns:
        a hash of local configuration items keyed by configuration item name
        Note:
        If any configuration items have an invalid type, an error is raised

      • updateStepData

        public static void updateStepData​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object> new_data)
                           throws java.lang.Throwable
        Updates the values of one or more keys in the workflow order data instance’s stepdata "dynamic step data hash" Dynamic step data is directly linked to the order data the workflow execution instance is processing. Changes are committed to the database before the method returns.
        Parameters:
        new_data - the key-value pairs to update in dynamic step data
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Since:
        Qorus 4.0.1
        See Also:
        stepdata, StepDataHelper
        Note:
        • his call does not replace the step data hash; any keys in the hash parameter are added to the step data hash
        • The use of this method causes SQL I/O to be performed in the system schema; to maximize performance, calls to this and other similar methods should be minimized if possible

      • deleteStepDataKey

        public static void deleteStepDataKey​(java.lang.String... keylist)
                              throws java.lang.Throwable
        Deletes one or more keys from the workflow order data instance’s stepdata "dynamic step data hash" Dynamic step data is directly linked to the order data the workflow execution instance is processing. Changes are committed to the database before the method returns.
        Parameters:
        keylist - a single key or a list of keys to delete in the workflow order's dynamic step data
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        Since:
        Qorus 4.0.1
        See Also:
        stepdata, StepDataHelper
        Note:
        The use of this method causes SQL I/O to be performed in the system schema; to maximize performance, calls to this and other similar methods should be minimized if possible
